  'about' => 
  array (
    'en_US' => '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Al-Musannif</strong> (print ISSN&nbsp;<a href="http://u.lipi.go.id/1556116208" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2657-2362</a>; online ISSN <a href="https://portal.issn.org/resource/ISSN/2684-7736" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2684-7736</a>) is an open-access peer-reviewed journal managed by the Faculty of Tarbiyah, <a href="http://staisddimangkoso.ac.id/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Institut Agama Islam DDI Mangkoso</a>, in collaboration with the <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_i82LqkfmfXH859oLwK87iBNTwr0qEGS/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Indonesian Islamic College Lecturers Association (ADPETIKISINDO)</a> and published by Madrasah Tsanawiyah DDI Cilellang as the laboratory school of the Faculty. Al-Musannif focuses its scope on the issues of <strong>Islamic education</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>education policy and management</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>teaching and student development</strong>, and<strong>&nbsp;community education</strong>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a title="Focus and Scope" href="https://jurnal.mtsddicilellang.sch.id/index.php/al-musannif/focus_scope" target="_blank" rel="noopener">all aspects</a>. We invite scientists, scholars, lecturers, researchers, educators, students, and other concerned parties to publish their works in our journal. The works should be original and take the form of high-quality empirical and theoretical research that provides references for readers to develop academic and scientific insights. The journal has been published biannually (in June and December) since 2019.<br>Al-Musannif is accredited (Grade/Sinta 4) by the Ministry of Education, Culture, Research, and Technology of the Republic of Indonesia under Number&nbsp;<a href="https://arjuna.kemdikbud.go.id/files/info/Hasil_Akreditasi_Jurnal_Ilmiah_Periode_III_Tahun_20226.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">225/E/KPT/2022</a>. The journal is a member of Crossref, so each article has a DOI number or a unique permanent